"use strict";(self.webpackChunkmobile_dev_docs=self.webpackChunkmobile_dev_docs||[]).push([[1477],{10:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"how-to-create-blog-post","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/how-to-create-blog-post","source":"@site/blog/2021-11-09-how-to-create-blog-post.mdx","title":"How to Create Blog Post","description":"Adding posts\u200b","date":"2021-11-09T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 9, 2021","tags":[{"label":"tutorial","permalink":"/blog/tags/tutorial"},{"label":"blog","permalink":"/blog/tags/blog"}],"readingTime":0.985,"truncated":true,"authors":[{"name":"M. Irfan Hidayat","title":"Software Engineer","url":"https://github.com/irufano","imageURL":"https://github.com/irufano.png","key":"irufano"}],"nextItem":{"title":"How to Create Docs Page","permalink":"/blog/how-to-create-docs-page"}},"content":"## Adding posts\u200b\\nTo publish in the blog, create a Markdown file within the blog directory.\\n\\nFor example, create a file at website/blog/2021-08-05-hello-blog.md\\n\\n```markdown title=\\"website/blog/2021-08-05-hello-blog.md\\"\\n---\\ntitle: Welcome Docusaurus v2\\ndescription: This is my first post on Docusaurus 2.\\nslug: welcome-docusaurus-v2\\nauthors:\\n  - name: Joel Marcey\\n    title: Co-creator of Docusaurus 1\\n    url: https://github.com/JoelMarcey\\n    image_url: https://github.com/JoelMarcey.png\\n  - name: S\xe9bastien Lorber\\n    title: Docusaurus maintainer\\n    url: https://sebastienlorber.com\\n    image_url: https://github.com/slorber.png\\ntags: [hello, docusaurus-v2]\\nimage: https://i.imgur.com/mErPwqL.png\\nhide_table_of_contents: false\\n---\\nWelcome to this blog. This blog is created with [**Docusaurus 2**](https://docusaurus.io/).\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nThis is my first post on Docusaurus 2.\\n\\nA whole bunch of exploration to follow.\\n```\\n\\n## Global authors\u200b\\nFor regular blog post authors, it can be tedious to maintain authors information inlined in each blog post.\\n\\nIt is possible declare those authors globally in a configuration file:\\n\\n```markdown title=\\"website/blog/authors.yml\\"\\njmarcey:\\n  name: Joel Marcey\\n  title: Co-creator of Docusaurus 1\\n  url: https://github.com/JoelMarcey\\n  image_url: https://github.com/JoelMarcey.png\\n\\nslorber:\\n  name: S\xe9bastien Lorber\\n  title: Docusaurus maintainer\\n  url: https://sebastienlorber.com\\n  image_url: https://github.com/slorber.png\\n```\\n\\nIn blog posts FrontMatter, you can reference the authors declared in the global configuration file:\\n\\nSingle author :\\n\\n```markdown title=\\"my-blog-post.md\\"\\n---\\nauthors: jmarcey\\n---\\n```\\n\\nMulti authors :\\n\\n```markdown title=\\"my-blog-post.md\\"\\n---\\nauthors: [jmarcey, slorber]\\n---\\n```"},{"id":"how-to-create-docs-page","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/how-to-create-docs-page","source":"@site/blog/2021-11-09-how-to-create-docs-page.mdx","title":"How to Create Docs Page","description":"Create a Markdown file, greeting.md, and place it under the docs directory.","date":"2021-11-09T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 9, 2021","tags":[{"label":"docs","permalink":"/blog/tags/docs"},{"label":"tutorial","permalink":"/blog/tags/tutorial"}],"readingTime":1.22,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"M. Irfan Hidayat","title":"Software Engineer","url":"https://github.com/irufano","imageURL":"https://github.com/irufano.png","key":"irufano"}],"prevItem":{"title":"How to Create Blog Post","permalink":"/blog/how-to-create-blog-post"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome to Blog","permalink":"/blog/welcome"}},"content":"Create a Markdown file, greeting.md, and place it under the docs directory.\\n\\n```\\nwebsite # root directory of your site\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 docs\\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 greeting.md\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 src\\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 pages\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 docusaurus.config.js\\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 ...\\n```\\n\\n## Example\\nIf you not define title system will take the head # of your md file to become title.\\n\\n\\n:::tip\\n`sidebar_position` is menu order at sidebar. \\n:::\\n\\n```markdown\\n---\\nsidebar_position: 1\\n---\\n\\n# introduction \\n\\n## Hello from Docusaurus\\n\\nAre you ready to create the documentation site for your open source project?\\n\\n### Headers\\n\\nwill show up on the table of contents on the upper right\\n\\nSo that your users will know what this page is all about without scrolling down or even without reading too much.\\n\\n### Only h2 and h3 will be in the toc by default.\\n\\nYou can configure the TOC heading levels either per-document or in the theme configuration.\\n\\nThe headers are well-spaced so that the hierarchy is clear.\\n\\n- lists will help you\\n- present the key points\\n- that you want your users to remember\\n  - and you may nest them\\n    - multiple times\\n\\n### Custom id headers {#custom-id}\\n\\n```\\n\\n## Doc tags\u200b\\nOptionally, you can add tags to your doc pages, which introduces another dimension of categorization in addition to the docs sidebar. Tags are passed in the front matter as a list of labels:\\n\\n```markdown\\n---\\nid: doc-with-tags\\ntitle: A doc with tags\\ntags:\\n  - Demo\\n  - Getting started\\n---\\n```"},{"id":"welcome","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/welcome","source":"@site/blog/2021-11-09-welcome/index.mdx","title":"Welcome to Blog","description":"Simply add Markdown files (or folders) to the blog directory.","date":"2021-11-09T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 9, 2021","tags":[{"label":"hello","permalink":"/blog/tags/hello"},{"label":"blog","permalink":"/blog/tags/blog"}],"readingTime":0.395,"truncated":false,"authors":[{"name":"M. Irfan Hidayat","title":"Software Engineer","url":"https://github.com/irufano","imageURL":"https://github.com/irufano.png","key":"irufano"}],"prevItem":{"title":"How to Create Docs Page","permalink":"/blog/how-to-create-docs-page"}},"content":"Simply add Markdown files (or folders) to the `blog` directory.\\n\\nRegular blog authors can be added to `authors.yml`.\\n\\nThe blog post date can be extracted from filenames, such as:\\n\\n- `2021-05-30-welcome.md`\\n- `2021-05-30-welcome/index.md`\\n\\nA blog post folder can be convenient to co-locate blog post images:\\n\\n![Docusaurus Plushie](./docusaurus-plushie-banner.jpeg)\\n\\nThe blog supports tags as well!\\n\\n:::tip\\n\\nUse the power of React to create interactive blog posts.\\n\\n```js\\n<button onClick={() => alert(\'button clicked!\')}>Click me!</button>\\n```\\n\\n<button onClick={() => alert(\'button clicked!\')}>Click me!</button>\\n\\n:::"}]}')}}]);